<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="363" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,294,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The new species differs from its allies by the forewing narrowly elongated, lacking costal patch; the hind wing with a yellowish transverse streak from near base to near basal 2/3 below discal cell. The male genitalia are also characterized by the shortly broadened uncus and the broad valva with a bunch of dense, long setae-like scales near lower base of cucullus, followed by much shorter setae along ventral margin to apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="363" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,438,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<figureCitation box="[427,563,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1969]" captionTargetBox="[171,1409,599,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-134@5.[151,1437,597,1922]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Thubdora pulchella Park &amp; Karisch, sp. nov.: A, Adult, holotype; A1, Labial palpus; A2, Label; B, Male genitalia, GU-3900/Karisch; B1, Aedeagus; C, Abdomen, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810516/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">Figs. 4A, A</figureCitation>
<figureCitation box="[563,578,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1836,1860]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,600,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-247@2.[151,1436,597,1813]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. A: View from Mt. Tonkoui over the anthropogenic influenced tropical rain forest on the slopes (by T. Karisch, 25 viii 1997); B: Collecting site for light trapping with altimontane rain forest fragments at the South-Eastern slopes of Mt. Tonkoui (by T. Karisch, 25 viii 1997; C: Fragmentary secondary rain forest south of Gouédié (by T. Karisch, 20 viii 1997); D: Collecting site at the Southern border of Gouédié (by T. Karisch, 17 viii 1997)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810510/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">2</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[719,887,438,465]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="1.75" metricValueMin="1.65" pageId="6" pageNumber="363" unit="mm" value="17.0" valueMax="17.5" valueMin="16.5">16.5–17.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[899,960,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">Head</emphasis>
: Brown dorsally. Antenna slightly shorter than forewing; scape elongated and broadened; flagellum yellowish-orange, with dark-brown annulations, slightly serrated, with fine cilia. Second palpomere of labial palpus thickened with rough scales ventrally, arched, yellowish-brown on outer surface, dark brown dorsally; 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[713,727,546,560]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">rd</superScript>
palpomere slender, strongly upturned, as long as 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1289,1305,546,560]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">nd</superScript>
palpomere, yellowish orange on outer surface. 
<emphasis box="[553,634,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">Thorax</emphasis>
: Glossy dark brown dorsally; tegulae with same color. Hind tibia yellowish white, dark brown in distal 1/4 of dorsal surface; spurs shiny yellowish white. Forewing ground color dark brown with a violet lustre; antemedian fascia blackish, irregularly shaped; costa slightly arched at basal third and before apex; apex obtuse; termen olique; fringe glossy dark brown, with a narrow, yellowish white basal line. Hind wing ground color as same as forewing, with yellowish white transverse streak along lower part of cell, suffused with yellowish white scales above costa; fringe concolorous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis box="[199,305,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[321,410,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1969]" captionTargetBox="[171,1409,599,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-134@5.[151,1437,597,1922]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Thubdora pulchella Park &amp; Karisch, sp. nov.: A, Adult, holotype; A1, Labial palpus; A2, Label; B, Male genitalia, GU-3900/Karisch; B1, Aedeagus; C, Abdomen, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810516/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
): Glossy dark brown dorsally, yellowish white ventrally; spinose zones on tergites well-developed with strong spines; abdominal tergite VIII with crescent sclerite; sternite with well-developed latero-caudal lobes anteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis box="[199,362,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[378,513,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1945,1969]" captionTargetBox="[171,1409,599,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-134@5.[151,1437,597,1922]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Thubdora pulchella Park &amp; Karisch, sp. nov.: A, Adult, holotype; A1, Labial palpus; A2, Label; B, Male genitalia, GU-3900/Karisch; B1, Aedeagus; C, Abdomen, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810516/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">Figs. 4B, B</figureCitation>
<figureCitation box="[512,523,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1276]" captionTargetId="figure-101@1.[151,1436,345,1276]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Topographical map of the region Northwest of Man, Black circles = collecting sites; inserted map: Ivory Coast with marked collecting area (arrow) (Openstreetmap, inserted map: Mapsland, CCA 3.0)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810508/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">1</figureCitation>
): Uncus short, broadened distally. Basal plate of gnathos more or less pentagonal with rounded caudal margin, exceeding apex of uncus. Valva broad; costa nearly straight and slightly concave in distal 2/3, with a bunch of dense, long setae-like scales near lower base of cucullus, followed by much shorter setae along ventral margin to apex; ventral margin arched, conjunction with cucullus not clearly defined; apex rounded. Juxta large, elliptical, membranous, lacking latero-caudal process. Vinculum narrow, banded. Aedeagus stout, narrowed toward apex from basal 3/5; cornuti consisting of a small bundle of setae and a large bundle of long setae beyond half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1221]" box="[199,401,1123,1149]" pageId="6" pageNumber="363">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
